text:
Lillestrøm Sportsklubb is a Norwegian professional football club from the city of Lillestrøm. The club was founded in 1917, after the merger of two local football clubs. The principal training ground is Lillestrøm stadion.
It has been Norwegian League champions five times, most recently in 1989, and also in 1986, 1977, 1976, and 1959. Additionally, they have won the Norwegian Cup in 1985, 1981, 1978, 1977, 2007 and 2017.
